{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"So earlier this year,"},{"time":2400,"text":"I was informed that I would be\ndoing a TED Talk."},{"time":6240,"text":"So I was excited, then I panicked,"},{"time":8240,"text":"then I was excited, then I panicked,"},{"time":10280,"text":"and in between the excitement\nand the panicking,"},{"time":12840,"text":"I started to do my research,"},{"time":15160,"text":"and my research primarily consisted\nof Googling how to give a great TED Talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20880,"text":"And interspersed with that,"},{"time":22560,"text":"I was Googling Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie."},{"time":25280,"text":"How many of you know who that is?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26920,"text":"(Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":29720,"text":"So I was Googling her\nbecause I always Google her"},{"time":32080,"text":"because I'm just a fan,"},{"time":33360,"text":"but also because she always has\nimportant and interesting things to say."},{"time":37000,"text":"And the combination of those searches"},{"time":40480,"text":"kept leading me to her talk"},{"time":43120,"text":"on the dangers of a single story,"},{"time":46320,"text":"on what happens\nwhen we have a solitary lens"},{"time":49720,"text":"through which to understand\ncertain groups of people,"},{"time":52240,"text":"and it is the perfect talk."},{"time":55720,"text":"It's the talk that I would have given\nif I had been famous first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62280,"text":"You know, and you know,\nlike, she's African and I'm African,"},{"time":65680,"text":"and she's a feminist and I'm a feminist,"},{"time":67640,"text":"and she's a storyteller\nand I'm a storyteller,"},{"time":69840,"text":"so I really felt like it's my talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":74440,"text":"So I decided that I was going\nto learn how to code,"},{"time":77760,"text":"and then I was going to hack the internet"},{"time":79800,"text":"and I would take down all the copies\nof that talk that existed,"},{"time":83560,"text":"and then I would memorize it,"},{"time":85000,"text":"and then I would come here\nand deliver it as if it was my own speech."},{"time":88280,"text":"So that plan was going really well,\nexcept the coding part,"},{"time":91480,"text":"and then one morning a few months ago,"},{"time":95400,"text":"I woke up"},{"time":97000,"text":"to the news that the wife\nof a certain presidential candidate"},{"time":102480,"text":"had given a speech that --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":105480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":107440,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112960,"text":"that sounded eerily like a speech\ngiven by one of my other faves,"},{"time":117600,"text":"Michelle Obama."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118840,"text":"(Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120960,"text":"And so I decided that I should\nprobably write my own TED Talk,"},{"time":125000,"text":"and so that is what I am here to do."},{"time":127520,"text":"I'm here to talk about\nmy own observations about storytelling."},{"time":132640,"text":"I want to talk to you\nabout the power of stories, of course,"},{"time":136640,"text":"but I also want to talk\nabout their limitations,"},{"time":139600,"text":"particularly for those of us\nwho are interested in social justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144280,"text":"So since Adichie gave that talk\nseven years ago,"},{"time":147200,"text":"there has been a boom in storytelling."},{"time":149480,"text":"Stories are everywhere,"},{"time":152240,"text":"and if there was a danger\nin the telling of one tired old tale,"},{"time":156200,"text":"then I think there has got to be\nlots to celebrate about the flourishing"},{"time":160560,"text":"of so many stories and so many voices."},{"time":163360,"text":"Stories are the antidote to bias."},{"time":166960,"text":"In fact, today, if you are middle class\nand connected via the internet,"},{"time":172040,"text":"you can download stories\nat the touch of a button"},{"time":175200,"text":"or the swipe of a screen."},{"time":176600,"text":"You can listen to a podcast"},{"time":178440,"text":"about what it's like\nto grow up Dalit in Kolkata."},{"time":182360,"text":"You can hear an indigenous\nman in Australia"},{"time":184880,"text":"talk about the trials and triumphs\nof raising his children in dignity"},{"time":189000,"text":"and in pride."},{"time":190360,"text":"Stories make us fall in love."},{"time":192360,"text":"They heal rifts and they bridge divides."},{"time":195560,"text":"Stories can even make it easier for us"},{"time":197440,"text":"to talk about the deaths\nof people in our societies"},{"time":200120,"text":"who don't matter,\nbecause they make us care."},{"time":202600,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204800,"text":"I'm not so sure,"},{"time":206080,"text":"and I actually work for a place\ncalled the Centre for Stories."},{"time":209840,"text":"And my job is to help to tell stories"},{"time":214280,"text":"that challenge mainstream narratives\nabout what it means to be black"},{"time":217840,"text":"or a Muslim or a refugee\nor any of those other categories"},{"time":220920,"text":"that we talk about all the time."},{"time":223960,"text":"But I come to this work"},{"time":225200,"text":"after a long history\nas a social justice activist,"},{"time":228720,"text":"and so I'm really interested in the ways"},{"time":230880,"text":"that people talk\nabout nonfiction storytelling"},{"time":233600,"text":"as though it's about\nmore than entertainment,"},{"time":235960,"text":"as though it's about being\na catalyst for social action."},{"time":239560,"text":"It's not uncommon to hear people say"},{"time":242240,"text":"that stories make\nthe world a better place."},{"time":246960,"text":"Increasingly, though, I worry\nthat even the most poignant stories,"},{"time":250200,"text":"particularly the stories about people\nwho no one seems to care about,"},{"time":254160,"text":"can often get in the way\nof action towards social justice."},{"time":257600,"text":"Now, this is not because\nstorytellers mean any harm."},{"time":261440,"text":"Quite the contrary."},{"time":262720,"text":"Storytellers are often do-gooders\nlike me and, I suspect, yourselves."},{"time":267600,"text":"And the audiences of storytellers"},{"time":270680,"text":"are often deeply compassionate\nand empathetic people."},{"time":274360,"text":"Still, good intentions\ncan have unintended consequences,"},{"time":279200,"text":"and so I want to propose that stories\nare not as magical as they seem."},{"time":283680,"text":"So three -- because\nit's always got to be three --"},{"time":286600,"text":"three reasons why I think"},{"time":288840,"text":"that stories don't necessarily\nmake the world a better place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294320,"text":"Firstly, stories can create\nan illusion of solidarity."},{"time":298400,"text":"There is nothing\nlike that feel-good factor you get"},{"time":300960,"text":"from listening to a fantastic story"},{"time":303120,"text":"where you feel like you\nclimbed that mountain, right,"},{"time":306520,"text":"or that you befriended\nthat death row inmate."},{"time":309840,"text":"But you didn't."},{"time":311280,"text":"You haven't done anything."},{"time":313120,"text":"Listening is an important"},{"time":314920,"text":"but insufficient step\ntowards social action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319120,"text":"Secondly, I think often we are drawn"},{"time":322000,"text":"towards characters and protagonists"},{"time":324960,"text":"who are likable and human."},{"time":328440,"text":"And this makes sense, of course, right?"},{"time":330360,"text":"Because if you like someone,\nthen you care about them."},{"time":333440,"text":"But the inverse is also true."},{"time":335400,"text":"If you don't like someone,"},{"time":337200,"text":"then you don't care about them."},{"time":339160,"text":"And if you don't care about them,"},{"time":341040,"text":"you don't have to see yourself\nas having a moral obligation"},{"time":344960,"text":"to think about the circumstances\nthat shaped their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"I learned this lesson\nwhen I was 14 years old."},{"time":352320,"text":"I learned that actually,\nyou don't have to like someone"},{"time":355120,"text":"to recognize their wisdom,"},{"time":356520,"text":"and you certainly\ndon't have to like someone"},{"time":358640,"text":"to take a stand by their side."},{"time":360800,"text":"So my bike was stolen"},{"time":363520,"text":"while I was riding it --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":366160,"text":"which is possible if you're\nriding slowly enough, which I was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":371280,"text":"So one minute\nI'm cutting across this field"},{"time":374280,"text":"in the Nairobi neighborhood\nwhere I grew up,"},{"time":376600,"text":"and it's like a very bumpy path,"},{"time":379080,"text":"and so when you're riding a bike,"},{"time":380920,"text":"you don't want to be like, you know --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":383200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":386160,"text":"And so I'm going like this,\nslowly pedaling,"},{"time":390800,"text":"and all of a sudden, I'm on the floor."},{"time":393400,"text":"I'm on the ground, and I look up,"},{"time":395600,"text":"and there's this kid peddling away\nin the getaway vehicle,"},{"time":398400,"text":"which is my bike,"},{"time":399920,"text":"and he's about 11 or 12 years old,\nand I'm on the floor,"},{"time":403200,"text":"and I'm crying because I saved\na lot of money for that bike,"},{"time":406080,"text":"and I'm crying and I stand up\nand I start screaming."},{"time":408680,"text":"Instinct steps in,\nand I start screaming, \"Mwizi, mwizi!\""},{"time":412960,"text":"which means \"thief\" in Swahili."},{"time":415560,"text":"And out of the woodworks,\nall of these people come out"},{"time":420600,"text":"and they start to give chase."},{"time":422040,"text":"This is Africa, so mob justice in action."},{"time":424320,"text":"Right?"},{"time":425800,"text":"And I round the corner,\nand they've captured him,"},{"time":428600,"text":"they've caught him."},{"time":430080,"text":"The suspect has been apprehended,"},{"time":432160,"text":"and they make him give me my bike back,"},{"time":435760,"text":"and they also make him apologize."},{"time":437400,"text":"Again, you know,\ntypical African justice, right?"},{"time":441000,"text":"And so they make him say sorry."},{"time":442520,"text":"And so we stand there facing each other,"},{"time":444880,"text":"and he looks at me, and he says sorry,"},{"time":447840,"text":"but he looks at me\nwith this unbridled fury."},{"time":451360,"text":"He is very, very angry."},{"time":455440,"text":"And it is the first time that I have been\nconfronted with someone"},{"time":458520,"text":"who doesn't like me\nsimply because of what I represent."},{"time":461160,"text":"He looks at me\nwith this look as if to say,"},{"time":463240,"text":"\"You, with your shiny skin\nand your bike, you're angry at me?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":469240,"text":"So it was a hard lesson\nthat he didn't like me,"},{"time":472520,"text":"but you know what, he was right."},{"time":474600,"text":"I was a middle-class kid\nliving in a poor country."},{"time":478120,"text":"I had a bike, and he barely had food."},{"time":481760,"text":"Sometimes, it's the messages\nthat we don't want to hear,"},{"time":484720,"text":"the ones that make us\nwant to crawl out of ourselves,"},{"time":487240,"text":"that we need to hear the most."},{"time":489840,"text":"For every lovable storyteller\nwho steals your heart,"},{"time":493040,"text":"there are hundreds more\nwhose voices are slurred and ragged,"},{"time":497440,"text":"who don't get to stand up on a stage\ndressed in fine clothes like this."},{"time":502640,"text":"There are a million\nangry-boy-on-a-bike stories"},{"time":506960,"text":"and we can't afford to ignore them"},{"time":508640,"text":"simply because we don't like\ntheir protagonists"},{"time":511800,"text":"or because that's not the kid\nthat we would bring home with us"},{"time":514760,"text":"from the orphanage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516600,"text":"The third reason that I think"},{"time":518480,"text":"that stories don't necessarily\nmake the world a better place"},{"time":522120,"text":"is that too often we are so invested\nin the personal narrative"},{"time":525600,"text":"that we forget\nto look at the bigger picture."},{"time":528880,"text":"And so we applaud someone"},{"time":530800,"text":"when they tell us\nabout their feelings of shame,"},{"time":533480,"text":"but we don't necessarily\nlink that to oppression."},{"time":537080,"text":"We nod understandingly\nwhen someone says they felt small,"},{"time":540760,"text":"but we don't link that to discrimination."},{"time":543600,"text":"The most important stories,\nespecially for social justice,"},{"time":546440,"text":"are those that do both,"},{"time":548280,"text":"that are both personal and allow us\nto explore and understand the political."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553920,"text":"But it's not just\nabout the stories we like"},{"time":555960,"text":"versus the stories we choose to ignore."},{"time":557880,"text":"Increasingly, we are living in a society\nwhere there are larger forces at play,"},{"time":561840,"text":"where stories are actually for many people\nbeginning to replace the news."},{"time":566640,"text":"Yeah?"},{"time":567880,"text":"We live in a time where we are witnessing\nthe decline of facts,"},{"time":571280,"text":"when emotions rule"},{"time":573520,"text":"and analysis, it's kind of boring, right?"},{"time":576640,"text":"Where we value what we feel\nmore than what we actually know."},{"time":582040,"text":"A recent report by the Pew Center\non trends in America"},{"time":586360,"text":"indicates that only 10 percent\nof young adults under the age of 30"},{"time":592160,"text":"\"place a lot of trust in the media.\""},{"time":595560,"text":"Now, this is significant."},{"time":597840,"text":"It means that storytellers\nare gaining trust"},{"time":600480,"text":"at precisely the same moment"},{"time":601880,"text":"that many in the media\nare losing the confidence in the public."},{"time":606040,"text":"This is not a good thing,"},{"time":608640,"text":"because while stories are important"},{"time":610440,"text":"and they help us\nto have insights in many ways,"},{"time":612680,"text":"we need the media."},{"time":614560,"text":"From my years\nas a social justice activist,"},{"time":617080,"text":"I know very well that we need\ncredible facts from media institutions"},{"time":623200,"text":"combined with the powerful voices\nof storytellers."},{"time":627240,"text":"That's what pushes the needle forward\nin terms of social justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631840,"text":"In the final analysis, of course,"},{"time":636480,"text":"it is justice"},{"time":638320,"text":"that makes the world a better place,"},{"time":640080,"text":"not stories. Right?"},{"time":643080,"text":"And so if it is justice that we are after,"},{"time":646160,"text":"then I think we mustn't focus\non the media or on storytellers."},{"time":649600,"text":"We must focus on audiences,"},{"time":652320,"text":"on anyone who has ever turned on a radio"},{"time":655440,"text":"or listened to a podcast,"},{"time":657280,"text":"and that means all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659400,"text":"So a few concluding thoughts"},{"time":661560,"text":"on what audiences can do\nto make the world a better place."},{"time":666000,"text":"So firstly, the world\nwould be a better place, I think,"},{"time":669960,"text":"if audiences were more curious\nand more skeptical"},{"time":673560,"text":"and asked more questions\nabout the social context"},{"time":676200,"text":"that created those stories\nthat they love so much."},{"time":680200,"text":"Secondly, the world\nwould be a better place"},{"time":682480,"text":"if audiences recognized\nthat storytelling is intellectual work."},{"time":687640,"text":"And I think it would\nbe important for audiences"},{"time":690600,"text":"to demand more buttons\non their favorite websites,"},{"time":695960,"text":"buttons for example that say,"},{"time":698680,"text":"\"If you liked this story,"},{"time":700320,"text":"click here to support a cause\nyour storyteller believes in.\""},{"time":704400,"text":"Or \"click here to contribute\nto your storyteller's next big idea.\""},{"time":710480,"text":"Often, we are committed to the platforms,"},{"time":713080,"text":"but not necessarily\nto the storytellers themselves."},{"time":715560,"text":"And then lastly, I think that audiences\ncan make the world a better place"},{"time":720680,"text":"by switching off their phones,"},{"time":723560,"text":"by stepping away from their screens"},{"time":725600,"text":"and stepping out into the real world\nbeyond what feels safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730840,"text":"Alice Walker has said,"},{"time":732880,"text":"\"Look closely at the present\nyou are constructing."},{"time":736680,"text":"It should look like the future\nyou are dreaming.\""},{"time":740640,"text":"Storytellers can help us to dream,"},{"time":742880,"text":"but it's up to all of us\nto have a plan for justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747480,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748720,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}